'''Abutilon mosaic virus'''  ('''AbMV''') is a virus of the genus [[Begomovirus]].  It infects [[Abutilon]] species, notably the flowering maple, ''[[Abutilon striatum]]''.  The mottled or variegated effect on the leaves is of ''Abutilon striatum'' is sought after.

==Vector==
The vector is a whitefly, ''[[Bemisia tabaci]]''.

==Strains==
* Abutilon mosaic A = West Indies virus
* Abutilon mosaic B = Brazil virus
* Abutilon mosaic Hawaii virus

